ğŸ§  Patterns / OPSEC Hints
ğŸ“‹ StickyNotes is a full DB. If you find plum.sqlite, assume there's loot inside.

ğŸ§© Look for .rdp or .config files on desktops â€” lazy devs leave creds.

ğŸ§¼ Clean up after copying/mounting .vmdk or .vhd â€” these scream â€œYOUâ€™RE CAUGHTâ€ in a real pentest.

ğŸ” If you see .kdbx files, go look for .key or plaintext passwords nearby â€” KeePass creds are often adjacent.

ğŸ§  Any folder like \\FILE01\users\bjones with loose perms is a jackpot â€” scrape them all.

ğŸ”‚ Once you're SYSTEM or admin, loop through every user profile and re-search.

